3 spells that strike me as just dumb pvp wise are...<br>
<br>
1. Epitath of Life lvl 52 cleric spell.  Magic based dot 750 damage over 30 seconds.  My guess is that this would be unresisable like the current magic based pure dmg dots splurt, winged death...magic based dots that are resistable normally include some other component like snare.<br>
<br>
2. Insidious Retrogression  lvl 49 necro spell diease based snare dot 560 damage over about a minute and a half<br>
<br>
3. Elnericks Entombment of Ice lvl 39 wiz spell max 340 dmg + root cold save.<br>
<br>
1-Not every class needs dots thanks I can just see the clerics running around casting that stupid dot and healing themselves while I pumice it.<br>
<br>
2 and 3- As a rogue in my opinion melee classes are only viable if they can resist root and snare this doesn't mean you will win but it does mean you have a chance.  Roots and snares become increasingly unbalancing in pvp combat as you get higher in levels if they actually stick (magic based ones don't at any reasonable lvl with decent mr gear).  <br>
<br>
Even at lvl 39 say the root hits ya for 230pvp and you are rooted for 12 seconds (can't pumice it) you could then eat the lvl 34dd also cold based for 210 x 3 for a total damage of 860 pvp damage<br>
